derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 17th cent. (denoting the main part of a pedestal, above the base): from Italian, literally dice or cube', from Latin datum 'something given, starting point' (see datum)

entry.def: A dado is a strip of wood that can be fixed to the lower part of a wall. The wall is then often decorated differently above and below the dado .

means.word_mean: 1. panel forming the lower part of an interior wall when it is finished differently from the rest
2. the section of a pedestal between the base and the surbase
3. a rectangular groove cut into a board so that another piece can fit into it
